description.narrative:
The Netherlands Ministry of Foreign Affairs (MOFA) and the consortium of organizations developing this project,  are part of Strategic Partnership, a 5 year program (2016-2020) which aims to ensure that in and by this partnership, civil society organizations (CSO) and civil society at large, both in the global South as well as in the overall global context, can contribute to decreasing inequality and injustice. A central objective is to counter the limited and decreasing political space for CSO around the world. 

To this end, the program proposes a Theory of Change focused on four pathways of change: 

1. Political space for CSO; 
2. Realizing the right to adequate food and nutrition; 
3. Small-producer empowerment and inclusive markets; 
4. Moving towards a sustainable private sector. 

These four pathways are interconnected, particularly in the case of Pathway 1, which  crosscuts the three other pathways. 

Project administration for this program in Mesoamerica is developed through a joint strategy in order to be able to influence national, regional and international spheres, to strengthen new leadership, develop capacities and alliances to support local actors and territorial government management.
